-- Erste Group Leads Czech Stock Rout on Moody’s Downgrade Warning
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-02-16T08:57:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/erste-group-leads-czech-stock-rout-on-moody-s-downgrade-warning.html
Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)  of Austria led
Czech stocks lower after Moody’s Investors Service said it may
lower the lender’s ratings.  The stock slumped 4.2 percent to 451 koruna by 9:43 a.m. in
 Prague , paring this year’s rally to 31 percent. The  PX (PX)  equity
index, where Erste has a 21 percent weighting, slid 2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  